The following splash/lua script concatenates all style sheets of the loaded webpage to a string and returns in. It runs fine the splash demopage (localhost:8050):
```lua
function main(splash, args)
  splash.images_enabled = false
  local get_stylesheet_rules = splash:jsfunc([[
  function () {
       var cssout = [];
       for (var i = 0; i < document.styleSheets.length; i++){
        var curStyleSheet = document.styleSheets[i];
            for (var j = 0; j < curStyleSheet.cssRules.length; j++){
                cssout.push(curStyleSheet.cssRules[j].cssText);
            }
       }
       return cssout.join('\n');
    }
  ]])
  splash:go(args.url)
  splash:wait(0.5)
  return get_stylesheet_rules ()
end
```
