Result from User testing summary:

We used bubbles linked by a line to representing the past commits, but this design confused users in the test.

1. Indicate where a commit should branch from
Correct Action: click bubble "1" 
1st time fail rate: 84.21%, 2nd time fail rate: 36.84%
--Clicked on HEAD commit in commit timeline (4), 
--Clicked on brand named origin/HEAD (3), 
--Clicked on the branch dropdown (2)

**Cause:** 
User cannot understand what the bubble means;
User cannot link the commit bubbles with the content below;

**Solution:**
Re-design: use green line to link bubble with content below;
Re-design sequence numbers inside bubbles; 
Animation for the ‘commit process’ and ‘open past commit process’;

